  <section class="introduction-section">
    <div class="container">
    <h1>Introduction</h1>
    <p>Hello! My name is Sarah, I like to write poetry, and I'm <strong></strong> interested in <a href="http://dirigiblestudio.com/">wind turbines</a> here in Ashburn, VA.
    <p/>
   
    <p>Climate change is a serious threat to our planet's health. I think it's important to switch to clean energy sources. <strong>One way is to use electricity </strong>, to power cars and homes. Electricity can come from clean sources such as solar and wind. <a href="https://www.rewiringamerica.org//">Rewiring America</a> is an organization with more information about converting to electric power.</p>
  </a>

  <section class="location-section">
    <div class="container">
    <h1>Wind</h1>
    <p>Wind can be harnessed by blades that spin to generate electricity in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wind_power#/media/File:Wind_power_plants_in_Xinjiang,_China.jpg">Virginia</a> my home. My favorite part about <b>Madison</b> is that we're a city built around a large <a href="http://www.wisc.edu/">university</a>. There's a vibrant crowd here that keeps this city bold and <strong>progressive</strong>. 
    
    The isles of <a href="http://www.quickmeme.com/img/50/50507a001a1b91078f63c8da7f340e9a529c7f22a65d0666ce1128bde8513d42.jpg">cheese</a> in every grocery store aren't so bad either.
      
    <p>You can find me in the city, <strong>camera</strong> in hand, documenting the stories around me, or in little cafe's writing about my daily <a href="http://www.kedarjoyner.com/blog/">adventures</a> and the people I meet.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="questions-section">
